            <p><add hand="#barker">Order for shot.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Saline </placeName><date when="1807-09-11">11th September 1807</date></p>
<p>Dr Sir,</p>

<p><persName>Mr. Charles L. Bird</persName> being unwell and at the <placeName>Lower Lick</placeName> requested
me this <date when="1807-09-11">Morning </date>to write to you for one 1 Kegg of the largest shot
that are made at your <placeName>workes</placeName>; the pay he desired me to inform you
would be ready at any time when call'd for. His wish is; that
youd- please to send it to this place by the return of <persName>Majr Hawkins</persName>
Waggon-Since Seeing <persName>Mr. Bird</persName>, I have spoke to <persName>Majr Hawkins</persName> about<pb n="137"/>
bringing the Kegg of Shot to this place, and <persName>Maj Hawkins</persName> requested
me to inform you, that it shall (If possible) be conveyed from your
works to his <placeName>Hutt</placeName>, I think the place is called <placeName>New discovery</placeName>.</p>

<p><persName>Majr Hawkins</persName>'s Waggon will bring you some Cart, of Waggon
Boxes, the weight neither the price do I no at this time; as I have
not removed to the works on the <placeName>opposite side of the Creek</placeName></p>

<p><persName>Duff Chadwell </persName>(?)
for <persName>Charles Lee Bird</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed.] <persName>Moses Austin Esquire</persName> <placeName>Mine A. Burton District of
St Genevieve</placeName> politeness <persName>Major Jno Hawkins</persName></p>


        </div1>
